Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.55,0:00:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to our program!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.09,0:00:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This month’s theme is
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.63,0:00:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Paying Attention?”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.13,0:00:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Strained relationships,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.60,0:00:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,illnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.13,0:00:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,careers,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.44,0:00:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,entertainment
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.80,0:00:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,—we’ll learn how to stay focused on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.08,0:00:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,despite these potential distractions.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.08,0:00:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll see how our ministry\Nis more effective
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.38,0:00:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,when we focus\Non reaching the hearts of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.49,0:00:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And our new song was written
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.49,0:00:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,especially for you young adults
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.09,0:00:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you keep your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.73,0:00:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,on the prize of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.76,0:00:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting®
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.40,0:00:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,for November 2020.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.85,0:01:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you paying attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.92,0:01:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you’ve been asked that question
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.99,0:01:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,by your parents, a teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.46,0:01:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,or someone else in authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.23,0:01:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a good question\Nfor each of us to ask ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.07,0:01:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you think\Nof occasions associated with our worship
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.70,0:01:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that require us to pay special attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.94,0:01:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, when reading the Bible,\Nattending meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.85,0:01:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,elders when shepherding,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.98,0:01:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you children\Nwhen being instructed by your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.19,0:01:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to pay attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.19,0:01:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet there are so many distractions
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.83,0:01:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,—electronic gadgets,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.83,0:01:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the conversations and activities\Nof those around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.76,0:01:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Truly, it can be a challenge\Nto pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.17,0:02:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know that the phrase “pay attention”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.24,0:02:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs dozens of times\Nin the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}New World Translation?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.91,0:02:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,In many of those occurrences,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.01,0:02:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is instructing his people\Nto pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.85,0:02:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean to “pay attention”?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.99,0:02:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And how important is it
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.36,0:02:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,that you and I pay attention to Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.09,0:02:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The account in 1 Samuel chapter 15
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.20,0:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,will help us to answer those questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 3, Jehovah instructs King Saul
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to strike down the Amalekites
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.97,0:02:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and to devote them\Nand everything they have to destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.58,0:02:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, verses 8 and 9 tell us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.92,0:02:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that Saul did not obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.12,0:02:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,He spared the king of Amalek
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.52,0:02:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the best of the animals.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.96,0:02:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,How did Saul respond
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.46,0:03:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when Samuel confronted him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.03,0:03:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As we read verses 13-15,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.47,0:03:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,note how Saul tried to justify\Nhis disobedience:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.41,0:03:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“When Samuel finally came to him,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.21,0:03:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Saul said to him:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.21,0:03:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘May Jehovah bless you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.41,0:03:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have carried out the word of Jehovah.’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.22,0:03:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“But Samuel said:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.25,0:03:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Then what is this sound\Nof the flock in my ears
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.29,0:03:31.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the sound of the cattle that I hear?’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.33,0:03:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“To this Saul said:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.63,0:03:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘They were brought from the Amalekites,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.87,0:03:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘because the people spared\Nthe best of the flock and the herd
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.44,0:03:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘for sacrificing them to Jehovah your God;
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.71,0:03:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but what was left\Nwe devoted to destruction.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.31,0:03:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.65,0:03:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Saul attempted to justify his disobedience,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.05,0:04:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,claiming that the animals\Nwould be sacrificed to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.93,0:04:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Was Jehovah pleased with Saul?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.09,0:04:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,As we read verse 22,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.43,0:04:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,please note the connection\Nbetween paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.40,0:04:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and obedience:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.80,0:04:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“Samuel then said:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.71,0:04:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Does Jehovah take as much pleasure\Nin burnt offerings and sacrifices
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.71,0:04:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘as in obeying the voice of Jehovah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.65,0:04:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.02,0:04:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘To obey is better than a sacrifice,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and to pay attention than the fat of rams.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What was one of the causes\Nof Saul’s disobedience?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.83,0:04:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He didn’t pay attention\Nto Jehovah’s instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.40,0:04:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,His failure to pay attention\Nresulted in disobedience
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and brought Jehovah’s disapproval.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.11,0:04:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What a powerful lesson for us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.35,0:04:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As happened with Saul,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.35,0:05:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,our worship\Ncould become unacceptable to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.85,0:05:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,if we fail to pay attention!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.26,0:05:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that we understand\Nwhy it is important to pay attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.10,0:05:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s consider\Nthree aspects of paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.83,0:05:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that are discussed in the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The first scripture we’ll consider
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.37,0:05:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is 2 Chronicles 19:6:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.68,0:05:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“And he [Jehoshaphat] said to the judges:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.65,0:05:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Pay attention to what you are doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.89,0:05:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘for you do not judge for man\Nbut for Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:45.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and he is with you when you pass judgment.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.63,0:05:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This admonition to “pay attention”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.27,0:05:52.27,Default,,0,0,0,,was given by King Jehoshaphat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.27,0:05:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to appointed judges\Nthroughout the land of Judah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.87,0:05:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What a sobering reminder!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Those judges had good reason
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.61,0:06:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay attention to what they were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.88,0:06:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.65,0:06:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They were responsible to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.69,0:06:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They represented him,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.69,0:06:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and their decisions\Naffected the lives of fellow worshippers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.26,0:06:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Thus, they needed to be familiar\Nwith Jehovah’s thinking on matters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.83,0:06:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and to hold to his unprejudiced viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.73,0:06:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,when handling matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.47,0:06:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This is an excellent reminder\Nfor those who serve as elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.74,0:06:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Good elders are good students of the Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.98,0:06:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and Bible-based publications.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.55,0:06:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.11,0:06:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Their attentiveness to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.15,0:06:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,enables them to pay attention\Nto what they are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.86,0:06:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If they are going to represent Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.36,0:06:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and reflect his thinking accurately\Nas they handle matters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.43,0:06:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—whether they’re shepherding\Nthe congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.23,0:06:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,delivering a part at a meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.63,0:07:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,caring for a challenging assignment,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.24,0:07:02.91,Default,,0,0,0,,or addressing wrongdoing
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.91,0:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—they must pay attention\Nto what they are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why they must be familiar\Nwith Jehovah’s thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.11,0:07:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and then take care to follow his direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.32,0:07:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If they do, they show\Nthat they are paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.19,0:07:21.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to what they are doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.06,0:07:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s interest in assisting the elders
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.09,0:07:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is demonstrated\Nin the ongoing education he provides.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.66,0:07:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Each time the circuit overseer\Nvisits the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.27,0:07:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,he presents material\Nprepared especially for the elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.14,0:07:41.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kingdom Ministry School\Nand the School for Congregation Elders
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.81,0:07:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,provide more intensive instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How important
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.52,0:07:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,that elders pay close attention to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.22,0:07:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and apply such instruction!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.62,0:07:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Their doing so protects,\Nnot just themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.39,0:07:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but also fellow worshippers.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.60,0:08:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,By paying attention, elders will be able
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.57,0:08:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to convey direction\Nto the congregations accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.30,0:08:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This can be especially important\Nif our worship is banned
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.07,0:08:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,or restricted\Nin the event of a natural disaster
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.08,0:08:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,or other catastrophic event.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.45,0:08:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us\Nto the second aspect of paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.98,0:08:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we’ll consider.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.02,0:08:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read Luke 8:18:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.66,0:08:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.26,0:08:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“pay attention to how you listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.77,0:08:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“for whoever has will be given more,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.94,0:08:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“but whoever does not have,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.04,0:08:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,even what he imagines he has\Nwill be taken away from him.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.21,0:08:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What did Jesus mean when he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.98,0:08:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“Pay attention to how you listen”?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.05,0:08:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Those in Jesus’ audience in the first century
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.82,0:09:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,had the wonderful privilege\Nof hearing Jesus’ literal voice
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.19,0:09:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as he instructed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we can’t hear\Nthe voice of Jesus today,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.07,0:09:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can read his words\Nand learn of his actions
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.30,0:09:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,as revealed in the Gospel accounts.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.77,0:09:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we have many opportunities to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.41,0:09:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah, Jesus,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.21,0:09:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“the faithful and discreet slave,”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.98,0:09:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders in our congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,our marriage mate, 
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.75,0:09:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and our children.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.99,0:09:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder the Bible writer James stated
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.59,0:09:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that “everyone must be quick to listen.”
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.53,0:09:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it:
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.53,0:09:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If Saul had truly listened receptively
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.20,0:09:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah’s direction\Nregarding the Amalekites,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.70,0:09:53.21,Default,,0,0,0,,he would likely have grasped\Nthe importance of the direction he received
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.21,0:09:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and would have been motivated to obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.75,0:09:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,However, his lack of attentiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.45,0:10:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,led to disobedience\Nand Jehovah’s disapproval.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.32,0:10:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don’t pay attention to how we listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.52,0:10:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,we could find ourselves becoming critical
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.73,0:10:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or unappreciative
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.73,0:10:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or even disobedient.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.20,0:10:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So as Jehovah instructs and directs us,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.04,0:10:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to think\Nabout what we are being told,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.37,0:10:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,ponder over its meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.61,0:10:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,mull it over in our mind\Nand, most important,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,apply the instruction in our own lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.35,0:10:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If you’re a young person,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.65,0:10:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you show that you’re paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.02,0:10:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to how you listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.69,0:10:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider the admonition\Nat Ephesians 6:1-3:
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.43,0:10:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“Children, be obedient to your parents
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.27,0:10:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“in union with the Lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.31,0:10:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“for this is righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.44,0:11:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Honor your father and your mother’
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.18,0:11:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“is the first command with a promise:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.91,0:11:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘That it may go well with you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.92,0:11:09.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you may remain a long time\Non the earth.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.62,0:11:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You children, who do you think\Nis the source of this direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that these words come from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice that the verses state not only
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.73,0:11:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that children\Nshould “be obedient” to their parents
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.74,0:11:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but also that they should\N“honor” their parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.04,0:11:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you show that you’re paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.85,0:11:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to how you listen to this direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.92,0:11:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was a boy, I can remember occasions
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,when my parents would ask me\Nto do something,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.99,0:11:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps to take out the trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I would always obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.86,0:11:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But at times, I’d make it very clear
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.60,0:12:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that I didn’t really want to do\Nwhat was asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.54,0:12:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you young ones know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.11,0:12:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,However, if we’re truly paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.78,0:12:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,to how we listen to Jehovah’s words,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.61,0:12:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll be careful to honor our parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.92,0:12:18.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which is an essential element of obedience.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.69,0:12:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, we contribute\Nto the peace of the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.89,0:12:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and we make Jehovah’s heart glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.73,0:12:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally,\Nas the promise in verse 3 indicates,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.03,0:12:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,paying attention to how you listen\Nwill protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.34,0:12:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and contribute to your success in other ways
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.54,0:12:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout your adult life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.68,0:12:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, all of us should remember
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.41,0:12:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that our everlasting welfare will depend
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on our willingness to listen and obey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.69,0:12:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,How important, then, that all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.59,0:12:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,pay attention to how we listen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.93,0:13:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The third aspect of paying attention is found
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.33,0:13:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,at Luke 21:34, 35:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.77,0:13:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“But pay attention to yourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“that your hearts never become weighed down
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.31,0:13:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,“with overeating and heavy drinking
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.08,0:13:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“and anxieties of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.75,0:13:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly that day\Nbe instantly upon you as a snare.”
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.19,0:13:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,When Jesus admonished his followers
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.63,0:13:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay attention to themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.76,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he didn’t have in mind the selfish thinking\Nthat characterized King Saul
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s so common, even encouraged,\Nin today’s world.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.14,0:13:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather, Jesus’ words reveal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.14,0:13:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that the key to paying attention to ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.51,0:13:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is knowing ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.12,0:13:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,—knowing what’s in our figurative heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.05,0:14:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a challenge for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.76,0:14:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.42,0:14:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible explains at Jeremiah 17:9:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.06,0:14:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“The heart is more treacherous\Nthan anything else
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.07,0:14:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“and is desperate.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.70,0:14:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can know it?”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.74,0:14:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 10 answers:
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“I, Jehovah, am searching the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.21,0:14:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,examining the innermost thoughts.”
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.15,0:14:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So Jehovah knows what is in our heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.99,0:14:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and he can help us to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.99,0:14:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He can help us to examine\Nour motives and goals
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and to discern why we do certain things.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.83,0:14:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Carefully and honestly looking at ourselves\Nin the mirror of God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.83,0:14:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,can reveal areas in our thinking, words,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.94,0:14:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and actions
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.94,0:14:53.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that need attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.01,0:14:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, some of Jehovah’s people
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.38,0:14:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,—including those of retirement age
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.48,0:15:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who have enjoyed\Nvery comfortable circumstances—
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.88,0:15:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,have concluded that they needed to make\Nadjustments in their lifestyle,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.89,0:15:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,simplifying their lives
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.06,0:15:12.16,Default,,0,0,0,,so that they can serve Jehovah more fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.16,0:15:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Some who have done so have had the privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.23,0:15:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of attending\Nthe School for Kingdom Evangelizers.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.03,0:15:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it meant\Nstepping out of their comfort zone,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.57,0:15:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps moving to a new congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.44,0:15:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,they’ve experienced Jehovah’s blessing\Nin ways that they couldn’t have anticipated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.45,0:15:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,as they share\Nthe benefits of their experience
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.42,0:15:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and theocratic education
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.59,0:15:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in their new assignments.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.69,0:15:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,How grateful we are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.69,0:15:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah is providing ongoing,\Nlife-saving instruction
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.86,0:15:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,by means of his Word and organization.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.70,0:15:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,May each of us be determined\Nto “pay attention”
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.50,0:15:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to what we are doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.57,0:15:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to how we listen,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:16:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and to ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.38,0:16:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,By doing so, we’ll avoid falling\Ninto the trap of disobedience
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.38,0:16:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as King Saul did.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.45,0:16:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, as attentive and obedient servants,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.29,0:16:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll enjoy Jehovah’s friendship forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.63,0:16:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Elders play an important role
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.00,0:16:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in helping us stay focused on Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.77,0:16:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly when we’re facing\Ndifficult problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.84,0:16:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In our first video,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.84,0:16:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how elders provide loving assistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.94,0:16:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything was going fine in my marriage
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.78,0:16:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—or so I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.75,0:16:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My ex-husband was disfellowshipped,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.15,0:16:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,left home
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.99,0:16:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and, in less than a month,\Nwe divorced.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.29,0:16:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after the divorce,\NI had to figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.96,0:16:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how I would provide for the girls,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.50,0:17:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so I began working as a cleaner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.27,0:17:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had to provide for them spiritually.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.35,0:17:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But many times,\Nbecause of discouragement and tiredness,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.88,0:17:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t be there for them\Nas much as they needed me to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.82,0:17:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides all of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.86,0:17:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had to deal\Nwith very negative feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.33,0:17:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a very difficult time in my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.17,0:17:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I had never been so sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.31,0:17:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t even get up to go to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.78,0:17:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To cope with this problem,\NI just kept praying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.22,0:17:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I was not able to walk,\Nand I was not able to get to the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.93,0:18:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders realized\Nthat I was missing from the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.24,0:18:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders quickly came to my aid.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.21,0:18:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that one of the things
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.34,0:18:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that touched me the most
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.38,0:18:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,was when the elders read a scripture.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.32,0:18:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 139:3:
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.22,0:18:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“You observe me when I travel\Nand when I lie down;
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.02,0:18:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,you are familiar with all my ways.”
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.86,0:18:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that I am precious to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It was as if Jehovah was healing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.60,0:18:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I now knew that Jehovah\Nwas interested in me
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.07,0:18:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he was looking after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.07,0:18:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He was making sure that I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.54,0:18:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else that I remember fondly
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.55,0:18:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,was after a meeting at the Kingdom Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.08,0:18:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the elders gave me\Nsome scriptures to read at home
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.25,0:19:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and said that if we needed any help,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.09,0:19:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the elders were there for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.09,0:19:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Two elders lovingly came to see me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.10,0:19:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because Jehovah uses them as shepherds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.90,0:19:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I live very far from the Kingdom Hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.67,0:19:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But the brothers made the sacrifice\Nto get public transport,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.24,0:19:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,get off at the main road,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.64,0:19:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and from there they walked 40 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.08,0:19:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to reach my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.82,0:19:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know what I would have done.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.75,0:19:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,When the elders arrived,\Nthey listened to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.32,0:19:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they cried with me,\Nand they read the Bible with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.60,0:19:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah loves me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.00,0:19:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When I started to feel better,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.24,0:19:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I went back to the group.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.20,0:19:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was really happy\Nto be back with my brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.95,0:20:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, after all the help we have received,\Nwe are doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.35,0:20:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The congregation is our second home,\Nand we feel very good there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.19,0:20:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I have today,\NI owe to the brothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.03,0:20:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.33,0:20:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I see shepherding calls\Nas a very evident way
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.14,0:20:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in which Jehovah demonstrates\Nhis full love for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.31,0:20:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that at times
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.54,0:20:30.41,Default,,0,0,0,,these visits might be\Na challenge for the elders,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.08,0:20:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but the results are really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.52,0:20:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt,\Nthey can see that all the work
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.52,0:20:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the effort is worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.59,0:20:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I will never forget the help\Nthat I received from the elders.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.16,0:20:47.43,Default,,0,0,0,,This situation taught me that Jehovah\Nwill not let his sheep get lost,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.43,0:20:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,not even one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.43,0:20:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jeremiah 23:4 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.07,0:20:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘And I will raise up over them shepherds
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.67,0:20:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘who will really shepherd them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.67,0:21:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘They will no longer be afraid or be terrified,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.04,0:21:02.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and none will be missing,’ declares Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.48,0:21:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,How did the elders help Mariana and Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As good shepherds,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.12,0:21:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,they were attentive to Jehovah’s flock,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.62,0:21:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so they were quick to notice\Nthat help was needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.99,0:21:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They visited Mariana and Elias\Nin their homes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.43,0:21:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,shared encouraging scriptures, and listened.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.10,0:21:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They showed that Jehovah\Ncares for every one of his sheep.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.11,0:21:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Those brothers,\Nlike the elders in your congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.58,0:21:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,paid attention\Nto the loving training and instruction
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.31,0:21:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they’d received from Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.25,0:21:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,To expand their ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.35,0:21:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,many Witnesses\Nhave learned another language.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.66,0:21:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.66,0:21:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, Jehovah knows\Nyour selfless effort and hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.43,0:21:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach and teach in that language.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.13,0:22:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But is preaching to people\Nin their native language
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.74,0:22:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sufficient to reach their heart?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.87,0:22:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s see in this dramatization.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.21,0:22:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Our family had been learning Chinese\Nfor over a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.42,0:22:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn’t easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.28,0:22:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,God has many titles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.49,0:22:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you know he has only one name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.66,0:22:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,[Speaking Chinese]
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.77,0:22:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ready, or at least I thought so.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.77,0:22:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Matthew!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.77,0:22:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I’ll be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.02,0:22:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We were making progress,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.29,0:22:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we weren’t giving up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.38,0:23:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed like most people\Njust weren’t interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.12,0:23:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We were not having a good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.13,0:23:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.90,0:23:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom and Liz weren’t having\Na good morning either.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.64,0:23:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother and Sister Lin joined us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.87,0:23:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They’ve been a big help to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.18,0:23:50.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We told them about our morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.55,0:23:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We were finally able to converse a little\Nand give presentations,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.32,0:23:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but everything seemed to fall flat.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.22,0:24:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You ask good questions at the door
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.02,0:24:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—but not always the right one.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.99,0:24:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, when you learn the language,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.36,0:24:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,do not forget to learn about people.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.60,0:24:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.17,0:24:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Our questions started conversations\Nin our old territory, but not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.44,0:24:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Your pronunciation is very good, see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.91,0:24:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Brother Lin.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.91,0:24:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We needed a different approach
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.72,0:24:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,where we didn’t just learn the language
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.85,0:24:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,but also how to reach the heart\Nof someone who speaks it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.09,0:24:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the July 2019 {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.63,0:24:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,we read about “Reaching the Hearts\Nof Nonreligious People.”
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.79,0:24:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice in paragraph 7,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.80,0:24:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,how do you think that we could be more\Nlike the apostle Paul?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.93,0:24:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Paul was a Jew,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.94,0:24:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,but when he was talking to other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.11,0:24:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,he had to adapt his presentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.47,0:24:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I like what 1 Corinthians 9:20-23 says:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.81,0:25:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“To the Jews I became as a Jew\Nin order to gain Jews;
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.62,0:25:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to those under law I became . . .”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.45,0:25:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Liz was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.55,0:25:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When Paul spoke to fellow Jews in Athens,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.29,0:25:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,he reasoned from the Scriptures.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.39,0:25:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But when he spoke to the Greeks\Nat the Areopagus, he adapted,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.13,0:25:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,reasoning with them first without the Bible.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.80,0:25:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He later wrote:
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.40,0:25:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have become all things\Nto people of all sorts,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.97,0:25:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I might by all possible means\Nsave some.”
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.68,0:25:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what we needed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.48,0:25:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned more about the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.29,0:25:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We started to listen more\Nand talk about things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.16,0:25:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that interested them.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.37,0:25:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We found different ways\Nto start conversations.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.54,0:26:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we kept learning more about the culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.61,0:26:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Part of a Chinese proverb I found says:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.48,0:26:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“He who comes near ink is stained black.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.65,0:26:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a great way to introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.65,0:26:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 13:20:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.72,0:26:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one walking with the wise\Nwill become wise.”
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.71,0:26:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It all comes down to showing love.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.56,0:26:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The more we paid attention\Nto how we were teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.70,0:26:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the more we were able to show people\Nthe God who loves them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.00,0:27:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful reminder\Nthat in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.17,0:27:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to pay attention to people
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.88,0:27:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,—to what interests them\Nand to what helps them!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.58,0:27:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we saw,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.62,0:27:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we may need to analyze\Nand adapt our teaching methods,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.65,0:27:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,just as Paul did.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.22,0:27:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Even as we endeavor to reach the hearts\Nof people in the ministry,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.23,0:27:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we must safeguard our own heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.60,0:27:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A recent {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower{\r} article
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.70,0:27:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,offered practical suggestions\Nto help us do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.40,0:27:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,In our next video,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.41,0:27:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,notice how our brothers\Nbenefited from applying what they learned.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.26,0:27:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, very good friends of ours
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.96,0:28:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,decided they wanted\Nto go their own way and leave Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.53,0:28:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the interim,\Nthey became bad association for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.54,0:28:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We had many good times together.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.97,0:28:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We drove to isolated territory together;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.21,0:28:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,we even visited a brother who was sick\Nin the hospital to encourage him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.12,0:28:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel heartbroken
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.12,0:28:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that they’re no longer serving Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.19,0:28:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s really hard to lose a friend spiritually\N—very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.79,0:28:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I was about to enter into full-time service,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.13,0:28:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but I still needed reassurance.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.20,0:28:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I was raised by my mother as a Witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.20,0:28:41.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though I had\Nvery little contact with my father,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.07,0:28:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,he still tried to oppose\Nmy spiritual progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.87,0:28:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I kept fighting for the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.57,0:28:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got baptized when I was 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.71,0:28:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess I felt like I was doing OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.15,0:28:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And after high school, I went to university.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.98,0:29:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to make some changes\Nin my choice of entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.99,0:29:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We really never stop learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.23,0:29:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I do enjoy relaxing and watching television.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.56,0:29:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But I must admit\Nthat it is more and more difficult
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.17,0:29:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to find something decent to watch these days.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.74,0:29:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m not saying\Nthat I watch bad programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.87,0:29:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I would never do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.38,0:29:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,but still I wonder
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.41,0:29:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if what I watch\Nis spiritually healthy for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.62,0:29:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The way of thinking\NI was exposed to in university
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.79,0:29:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,was pressuring me to find security in my life\Nthrough material things
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.26,0:29:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,—like having my own place to live\Nand economic stability.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.30,0:29:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But at what cost?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.04,0:29:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember that paragraph.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.24,0:29:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It said that Satan promotes making money
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.41,0:29:58.41,Default,,0,0,0,,as the only way
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.41,0:30:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you can find security in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.55,0:30:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But one could sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.55,0:30:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,so much to achieve it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.09,0:30:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You could even lose
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.15,0:30:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,your friendship with Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.55,0:30:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That article—it was just what we needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.99,0:30:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It described a watchman
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.13,0:30:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,who would protect the city
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.76,0:30:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,by sounding out an alarm on impending danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.63,0:30:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And at sounding that alarm,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.80,0:30:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,he would shut the gates\Nto the city to protect the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.97,0:30:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I needed to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.74,0:30:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We both needed to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.18,0:30:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.18,0:30:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s not even a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.58,0:30:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Our loyalty to Jehovah comes first
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.68,0:30:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,—before we’re loyal\Nto any friends we have in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.45,0:30:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r}  said
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.46,0:30:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that storytelling
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.46,0:30:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,does more than entertain us.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.70,0:30:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,In Bana, the city of Cameroon\Nwhere I was born,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.43,0:30:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,mothers spend their evenings\Nwith their children, telling them stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.44,0:30:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And even though I was young,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.47,0:31:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the stories my mother told me
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.68,0:31:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,continue to influence me even today.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.65,0:31:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So I said to myself: ‘Oh, no.\NWait a minute, Happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.18,0:31:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,‘It means that the stories\Nthat I watch on television
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.86,0:31:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,‘will also affect me sooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.16,0:31:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Devil knows that too.’
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.46,0:31:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So I decided to completely cut out a number
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.30,0:31:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of programs that I used to watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.07,0:31:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I’m serving in full-time service,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.14,0:31:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.14,0:31:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is really taking care of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.31,0:31:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don’t want to forget
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.31,0:31:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the beautiful principles\NI’ve learned from that article.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.88,0:31:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I still have to safeguard my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.82,0:31:46.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to give my best to my Father, Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.52,0:31:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a day goes by where we don’t think\Nabout these friends of ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.36,0:31:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s certainly our hope\Nthat they come back to Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.73,0:31:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we can serve Jehovah\Ntogether shoulder to shoulder.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.93,0:31:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But we’ve also learned
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.10,0:32:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep our “little watchman” in check.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.67,0:32:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to make sure he does his job\Nto “sound the alarm” and “shut those gates.”
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.41,0:32:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, we never stop learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.94,0:32:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, true, it’s easier said than done,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.11,0:32:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but it is up to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.45,0:32:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s so important to safeguard your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.77,0:32:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We all enjoy reading {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.20,0:32:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and commenting at the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower{\r}  Study.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.27,0:32:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But truly paying attention
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.54,0:32:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,means putting what we learn into action.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.25,0:32:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What else goes\Ninto being a discerning student?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.82,0:32:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the topic\Nof a recent Morning Worship program
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.75,0:32:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,presented by Brother Joel Dellinger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.86,0:32:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Our focus in the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower{\r} study article
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.09,0:33:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is on how we can unleash
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.70,0:33:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of God’s Word
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.26,0:33:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when teaching from the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.47,0:33:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But, you know, whether we’re teaching
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.14,0:33:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in a congregation setting,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.17,0:33:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,on a Bible study, or in the family,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.94,0:33:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,isn’t it true that all of us,\Nbrothers and sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.94,0:33:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,need to ‘pay constant attention\Nto ourselves and to our teaching’?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.98,0:33:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And we know why that’s so important\N—because lives are at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.55,0:33:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of us, younger or older,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.16,0:33:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,touch the lives of other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.49,0:33:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we teach effectively,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.79,0:33:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we are giving opportunity to others
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.73,0:33:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to attain the wisdom and the discernment\Nthat God’s Word can give them.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.07,0:33:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why we need to approach\Nany teaching opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.40,0:33:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,seriously and prayerfully.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.97,0:33:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 20 years ago, a kind elder gave me
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.08,0:33:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,some constructive counsel\Nafter a public talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.38,0:33:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, with a warm smile, he said this,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.45,0:33:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember, none of us teach like Jesus did.”
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.42,0:34:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’ll never forget that counsel.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.06,0:34:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were those observations so helpful?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.29,0:34:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it reminded me that when teaching,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.83,0:34:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,our model needs to be Jesus,\Nthe Great Teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.07,0:34:14.27,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s more to learn from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.27,0:34:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jesus’ example reminds us of the need
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.07,0:34:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to remain humble and diligent\Nstudents of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.71,0:34:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,—the Grand Instructor.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.81,0:34:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Though all of us are teachers on occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.12,0:34:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,isn’t it true that most often
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.25,0:34:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the role we play during spiritual programs
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.86,0:34:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is that of students?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.56,0:34:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for a moment, think about the many hours
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.06,0:34:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we spend as students\N—not teachers—
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.10,0:34:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re in the audience\Nat congregation meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.14,0:34:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,at assemblies, and at conventions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.04,0:34:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Add to that the time we are students
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.27,0:34:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,when we buy out time to watch\Nthe monthly broadcast,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.88,0:35:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to prepare for meetings,\Nto engage in family and personal study.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.25,0:35:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then think of the added privilege\Nthat many of us here have
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.05,0:35:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,—to enjoy morning worship five days a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.39,0:35:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, a typical program\Nof morning worship
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.49,0:35:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,lasts between 20 to 25 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.10,0:35:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you multiply that by 5 days a week\Nand then by 52 weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.40,0:35:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at a minimum, we are exposed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.20,0:35:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,to at least 86 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.54,0:35:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of divine instruction each year.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.74,0:35:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But if we’re not careful,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.74,0:35:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,some or much of that valuable instruction,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.01,0:35:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,encouragement, and counsel\Ncould just wash over us.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.52,0:35:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So for the remaining time\Nfor our program this morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.02,0:35:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s consider some things all of us can do
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.56,0:35:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen more effectively
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.16,0:35:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at spiritual programs.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.86,0:35:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, for our first point, open your Bible
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.10,0:35:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to Ezra 7:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.33,0:35:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and let’s consider Ezra’s example.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.64,0:36:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Ezra 7:10,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.14,0:36:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and notice the reading carefully:
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.85,0:36:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,“Ezra had prepared his heart
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.01,0:36:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“to consult the Law of Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.52,0:36:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to practice it,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.52,0:36:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to teach its regulations
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.72,0:36:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and judgments in Israel.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.72,0:36:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you have the Bible with the asterisk
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.86,0:36:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,next to “prepared his heart,”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.06,0:36:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if you tap on that, you’ll notice\Nthat that could be rendered as
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.00,0:36:29.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“had determined in his heart.”
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.17,0:36:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what do we learn from Ezra?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.17,0:36:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the right attitude\Ngoing into a period of study.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.61,0:36:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the right approach\Nto study and learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.18,0:36:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He recognized that it was Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.88,0:36:44.45,Default,,0,0,0,,who would be teaching him through His Law.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.45,0:36:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And as the verse goes on to say,\Nhe first recognized
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.16,0:36:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,that he needed to personally practice\Nwhat he was learning.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.06,0:36:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then would he be in a rightful position
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.13,0:36:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to effectively teach others.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.93,0:37:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this scripture emphasizes the point\Nwe’ve already made, doesn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.94,0:37:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Though we are teachers on occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.67,0:37:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we are always first and foremost
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.58,0:37:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,students of God’s Word.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.55,0:37:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we imitate Ezra’s example
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.71,0:37:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and prepare our hearts before study,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.69,0:37:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,before attending a spiritual program
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.89,0:37:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,(whether here at Bethel\Nor in the congregation),
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.72,0:37:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,before watching a monthly broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.26,0:37:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we need to prepare our hearts\Nby specifically praying to Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.27,0:37:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,recognizing him\Nas the Source of the teaching.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.64,0:37:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we pray specifically about?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.81,0:37:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, for one, we want to pray\Nthat we remain humble
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.48,0:37:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,while listening to theocratic instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.45,0:37:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to listen
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.45,0:37:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,—no matter how long\Nwe’ve been in Jehovah’s classroom—
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.75,0:37:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,because none of us know it all,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.42,0:37:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,nor will we ever know it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.76,0:37:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Proverbs 1:5 reminds us
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.03,0:38:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that “a wise person listens\Nand takes in more instruction.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.57,0:38:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, this leads to another question:
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.73,0:38:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What if we find we have\Na somewhat negative attitude
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.74,0:38:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,toward a certain presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.07,0:38:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,—perhaps the material doesn’t interest us,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.58,0:38:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,or we have a negative attitude\Ntoward a certain brother
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.01,0:38:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and his teaching ability?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.05,0:38:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.05,0:38:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Prepare our heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.09,0:38:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to Jehovah\Nto recognize and appreciate
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.26,0:38:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that the instruction is from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.63,0:38:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray to have a thankful spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.56,0:38:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, back in 2002,\N{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower{\r}  made this helpful point
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.47,0:38:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in an article that was entitled\N“Pay More Than the Usual Attention.”
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.97,0:38:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I quote: “Some may tend to gauge\Nthe quality of a meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.21,0:38:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“by the teaching abilities\Nof the participants. . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.21,0:38:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“Though the teaching ability\Nof participants is important,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.41,0:38:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“it is not the sole factor contributing\Nto a meeting’s success.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.69,0:39:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you not agree\Nthat our prime concern should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.86,0:39:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,“not how well the speaker delivers his talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.89,0:39:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,“but how well we incline our ear?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.63,0:39:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,When we attend meetings,”\Nthe article continues,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.60,0:39:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“and pay attention\Nto what is being presented,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.23,0:39:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“we are worshiping God\Nin harmony with his will.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.17,0:39:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“That is what makes the meeting a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.14,0:39:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“If we are eager\Nto take in the knowledge of God,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.71,0:39:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“we will benefit from meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.74,0:39:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,regardless of a speaker’s abilities.”
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.35,0:39:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful reminder for all of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.98,0:39:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So our first point: Like Ezra,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.32,0:39:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s prepare our hearts with prayer,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.96,0:39:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as students who are determined to always
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.99,0:39:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,accept and apply\Nwhat Jehovah has to teach us.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.17,0:39:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider a second point:
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.27,0:39:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the need to focus our attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.64,0:39:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you faced the challenge\Nof staying focused
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.41,0:39:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,during spiritual programs?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.91,0:39:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our minds may be distracted
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.51,0:40:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,with anxieties and many other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.55,0:40:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Noise and movements around us\Ncould distract us.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.32,0:40:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re watching morning worship 
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.32,0:40:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,at a location other than\Nthe Bethel dining room,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.76,0:40:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,likely we well know the numerous distractions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.69,0:40:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that fight for our attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.20,0:40:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of us have ailments\Nand physical discomforts
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.90,0:40:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that may make it difficult to concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.53,0:40:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, a sister in our congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.20,0:40:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,told us about her long-term battle\Nwith migraine headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.98,0:40:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to put myself in her shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.64,0:40:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,having a migraine headache\Nwhile attending a spiritual program
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.82,0:40:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,—difficult to concentrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.15,0:40:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, whatever the case may be, we know\N—we admit—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.22,0:40:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,that there are many challenges\Nand distractions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.06,0:40:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What can we do about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.06,0:40:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, since the eyes strongly influence
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.09,0:40:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,where we focus our attention,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.20,0:40:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Benefit{\r}  book provides this suggestion:
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.10,0:40:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“Use your eyes to help you concentrate\Nby keeping them on the speaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.80,0:40:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“When he cites a Bible text\N—even a familiar one—
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.47,0:41:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,look it up, and follow along as he reads it.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.34,0:41:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it said this:\N“Resist the temptation to turn your head
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.91,0:41:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the direction of every noise or movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.82,0:41:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“If the eyes are flooding your mind\Nwith distracting information,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.82,0:41:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,you will miss much\Nof what is presented from the platform.”
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.06,0:41:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And think about, too,\Nthe use of electronic devices.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.73,0:41:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever been alerted,\Nmessaged, or e-mailed
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.03,0:41:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,while looking at the Bible on your device?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.44,0:41:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,How wise it is when we turn\Nthose devices to a mode
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.24,0:41:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that eliminates unnecessary distractions!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.65,0:41:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what about anxieties\Nor disquieting thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.18,0:41:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What could we do about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.68,0:41:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here, again, is where we can remember
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.32,0:41:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who the Grand Instructor is\Nand how close he can be to us
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.56,0:41:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,when we’re in a teaching environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.69,0:41:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Open, please, your Bible to Psalm 94:19
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.26,0:42:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to recall what the psalmist said to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.10,0:42:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At Psalm 94:19,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.17,0:42:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,we read:
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.18,0:42:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“When anxieties overwhelmed me,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.68,0:42:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you [Jehovah] comforted and soothed me.”
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.28,0:42:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What a beautiful reminder!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.82,0:42:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah can soothe and comfort us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.49,0:42:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,when attending spiritual programs
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.76,0:42:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can focus\Non what he’s teaching us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.53,0:42:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, spiritual programs\Nare a provision from him
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.03,0:42:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,—a spiritual lifeline.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.23,0:42:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So as needed during a spiritual program,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.47,0:42:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,we should pray to Jehovah\Nto help us stay focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.57,0:42:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Pray repeatedly as needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.64,0:42:44.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in summary, what have we learned?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.91,0:42:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All of us are teachers from time to time,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.92,0:42:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,but first and foremost, we are students
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.75,0:42:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,in the classroom of the Great Teacher\Nand the Grand Instructor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.66,0:42:58.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Ezra, humility and appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.49,0:43:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,should move us to ‘prepare our hearts’\Nbefore every spiritual program.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.96,0:43:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We don’t want to miss anything
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.97,0:43:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that Jehovah has for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.70,0:43:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re determined ‘to consult that Law
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.70,0:43:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can practice it\Nand then teach it.’
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.97,0:43:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And in view\Nof all the potential distractions,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.44,0:43:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s make it our aim to use\Nour eyes, our mind, and our heart
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.78,0:43:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to focus attention on the goodness\Nof Jehovah’s spiritual provisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.66,0:43:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you are a young Christian\Nwho recently graduated from school
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.69,0:43:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,or will soon graduate,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.93,0:43:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ll make many decisions\Nthat will affect your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.03,0:43:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How, though, can you make decisions
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.17,0:43:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that let you\Nsuccessfully run the race for life?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.71,0:43:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the subject of our new music video.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.91,0:43:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t look back\NTo the things behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.12,0:44:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your eyes straight ahead\NOn that finish line.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.60,0:44:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now’s the time to be strong.\NKeep building your faith.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.47,0:44:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t let the world\Nslow you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.88,0:44:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Put off ev’ry weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.72,0:44:34.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s\NRun the race; run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.22,0:44:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race\Nfor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.72,0:44:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race;\Nyes, run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.66,0:44:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your eye\Non the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.73,0:44:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race;\Nrun the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.03,0:44:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got to keep on going—\NGot to keep on moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:46.70,0:44:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race.\NLet’s run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.67,0:44:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The prize we gain—\NIt’ll never fade away.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.98,0:45:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,All the blessings in store—\NSoon we’ll see the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.99,0:45:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s\NRun the race; run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.43,0:45:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race\Nfor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.73,0:45:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race;\Nyes, run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.23,0:45:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your eye\Non the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.84,0:45:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race;\Nrun the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.24,0:45:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got to keep on going—\NGot to keep on moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.61,0:45:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race.\NLet’s run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.44,0:45:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race\Nfor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.05,0:45:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,This world would like\Nto have you turn around
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.29,0:45:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And lose yourself in this life.\NBut don’t let your hands drop down.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.06,0:45:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s\NRun the race; run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.40,0:45:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race;\Nrun the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:46:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So let’s\NRun the race; run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.98,0:46:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race\Nfor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.28,0:46:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race;\Nyes, run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.38,0:46:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep your eye\Non the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.28,0:46:11.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race;\Nrun the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.65,0:46:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got to keep on going—\NGot to keep on moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.22,0:46:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s run the race.\NLet’s run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.83,0:46:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race for life.\NRun the race for life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.47,0:46:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ve got to run the race, yes.\NCome on, and run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.44,0:46:40.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race.\NLet’s run the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.41,0:46:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Run the race.\NRun the race for life!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.56,0:46:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Volunteering\Nfor theocratic construction projects
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.79,0:46:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is a goal for many.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.80,0:46:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Recently, thousands of brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.43,0:47:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrificed their time and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.07,0:47:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to build a beautiful new\Nbranch facility in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.57,0:47:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to see\Nthe results of their hard work
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.91,0:47:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and the blessings they received?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.41,0:47:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Please enjoy this report.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.82,0:47:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,How will you feel\Nwhen all we came here to do
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.89,0:47:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is finally completed?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.52,0:47:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt, we will find a moment to reflect
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.69,0:47:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,on the words of Philippians 2:13.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.23,0:47:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Jehovah energized us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.40,0:47:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and gave each and every one of us\N“both the desire
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.20,0:47:37.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power to act.”
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.27,0:47:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,How has sharing on this project\Naffected your life?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.58,0:47:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It all started over seven years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.89,0:48:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you imagine how excited\Nyou’re going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.36,0:48:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,when we hear\Nthat the new branch facility at Chelmsford
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.04,0:48:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,has been approved by the City Council?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.97,0:48:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, guess what?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.21,0:48:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday afternoon we received the approval.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.46,0:50:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whilst the buildings are beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.30,0:50:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,at the end of the day,\Nthey are just buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.73,0:50:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The really special part of this project
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.87,0:50:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,has been the people;
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.87,0:51:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,even non-Witnesses saw that something special
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.24,0:51:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was taking place on our site.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.64,0:51:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a very friendly site to work on.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.88,0:51:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just how friendly everyone is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.88,0:51:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk in, and it just—\NI find it mind-blowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.32,0:51:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,In a negative (sometimes) society,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.25,0:51:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,when you come here,\Nit just puts a smile on your face.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.39,0:51:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A truly unexpected success
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.09,0:51:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,was the visitors’ center.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.39,0:51:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How we underestimated the appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.76,0:51:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s people have
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.10,0:51:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,for theocratic activities.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.17,0:51:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Visitors from all around the globe witnessed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.50,0:51:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the activities of Jehovah for themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.94,0:51:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is partly why
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.94,0:51:39.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m actually studying the Bible\Nto get baptized,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.51,0:51:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because when I came here,\Nit just hit me somewhere, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.68,0:51:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Alicia can’t see,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.55,0:51:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,so everyone has been\Nso encouraging and thoughtful.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.19,0:51:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We really feel like Jehovah is with us\Nand he’s supported us.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.30,0:51:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I really liked the ladies driving tractors.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.77,0:52:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone wanted to have\Na part in the project.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.04,0:52:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Every single contribution warmed our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.38,0:52:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and sometimes our heads too.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.48,0:52:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Another beautiful project highlight
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.35,0:52:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,was the day-volunteer program.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.35,0:52:20.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The effort and expense brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.45,0:52:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sacrificed reminded all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.92,0:52:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of what a privilege it is\Nto work for Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.63,0:52:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And how about the commuters\Nwho helped on the project?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.76,0:52:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Would the BRD family have had
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.17,0:52:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the same spirit without our commuters?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.17,0:52:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t you just love being a part\Nof this amazing family?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.18,0:52:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We were regularly reminded that spirituality
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.62,0:52:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is of the utmost importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.65,0:52:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you ever say that a monthly meeting
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.65,0:52:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,was the best one yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.52,0:53:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What lies outside the comfort zone
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.36,0:53:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is the faith zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.56,0:53:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t cry because it’s over;
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.00,0:53:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,smile because it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.97,0:53:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your story?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.34,0:53:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The center of all of our stories is Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.54,0:53:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one who energized us;
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.35,0:53:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,he is the one who gave us\Nboth the desire
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.05,0:53:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the power to act.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.42,0:53:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one we can thank
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.62,0:53:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the lifelong friendships we have formed,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.59,0:53:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the training we have received,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.39,0:53:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the challenges\Nwe have been able to overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.99,0:53:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember your story.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.96,0:53:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, it’s only just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.44,0:53:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In this month’s program,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.51,0:53:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned what it means\Nto pay attention to Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.88,0:53:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw how we can stay focused on Jehovah
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.69,0:54:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,despite potential distractions.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.36,0:54:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Elders are good shepherds
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.29,0:54:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are attentive\Nto Jehovah’s instruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.63,0:54:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ministry is more effective
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.77,0:54:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when we focus\Non reaching the hearts of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.20,0:54:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And our new song
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.74,0:54:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,reminds our young adults\Nto keep their eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.64,0:54:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,on the prize of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.15,0:54:29.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we say goodbye,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.55,0:54:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s go to the southwest tip of Japan
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.39,0:54:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and visit our brothers and sisters\Nin the Ishigaki Congregation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.59,0:54:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Their territory includes the Yaeyama Islands,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.43,0:54:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,an archipelago
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.43,0:54:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,of 12 islands\Nand more than 360 coral reefs.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.83,0:54:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Emerald-green waters\Nsurround these lush,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.64,0:54:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,jungle-covered islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.64,0:54:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With almost no light pollution,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.84,0:54:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,this is an ideal place to observe
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.21,0:55:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s beautiful heavenly creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.48,0:55:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Vast distances between the islands\Nmake the ministry a challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.39,0:55:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To reach remote communities,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.06,0:55:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,publishers take ferries and small airplanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.06,0:55:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This is costly,\Nand economic conditions here aren’t easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.50,0:55:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Transportation includes bicycles
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.34,0:55:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as carts and wagons\Npulled by water buffalo.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.21,0:55:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Public witnessing is an effective way
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.28,0:55:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to share the good news
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.51,0:55:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with the many tourists who travel here.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.52,0:55:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,More than one million
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.55,0:55:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,visited during one recent year.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.12,0:55:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Contact cards also produce good results.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.13,0:55:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Ishigaki Congregation has 112 publishers,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.40,0:55:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,including 35 regular pioneers.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.40,0:55:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re conducting\Nmore than 100 Bible studies every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.47,0:56:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kingdom Hall\Nis in Ishigaki City on the main island.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.51,0:56:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Talks from this Kingdom Hall
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.81,0:56:08.65,Default,,0,0,0,,are streamed to this small meeting place
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.65,0:56:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,for the seven brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.78,0:56:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who live on remote Iriomote Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.76,0:56:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The publishers work together\Nto maintain the Kingdom Hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.96,0:56:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and they enjoy upbuilding association
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.53,0:56:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in this beautiful land.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.50,0:56:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters\Nin the Ishigaki Congregation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.37,0:56:32.41,Default,,0,0,0,,send their warm love and greetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.41,0:56:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,From the World Headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.31,0:56:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of Jehovah’s Witnesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.31,0:56:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting.
